<TITLE> Situation on Indian border `fragile': Pakistani PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ISLAMABAD, Fri Jan 9, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistani Prime Minister Yousaf Raza Gilani said on Friday the situation was `fragile' on the border with India, and regretted the suspension of peace talks following the militant attacks in Mumbai in November. Gilani's remarks came a day after the government confirmed that the lone surviving gunman from the attack that killed 179 people in India's financial capital was a Pakistani. The prime minister sacked his national security adviser on Thursday for disclosing this before consulting him. "The situation on our eastern border has once again become very fragile," Gilani told a seminar in Islamabad
